Description: there has been explosive growth in a new market called Personal Manufacturing.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Over the past decade, there has been explosive growth in a new market called Personal Manufacturing. Now, it has become possible for someone in a basement or makerspace to bring any idea to life in a handful of weekends with a handful of tools. Nonetheless, entering this empowering field is prohibitive for certain groups such as educators in matters of both cost and expertise. OTS Co. seeks to remove those barriers and allow everyone to get their feet wet with personal manufacturing, empowering the DIY spirit and democratizing the world of making. Ottia is a first-in-class “Maker Machine” which unifies cutting-edge technologies from 3D-Printing to computer-controlled cake-frosting all within one device. Ottia is designed to be simple and welcoming for newcomers, while also being highly capable for seasoned makers. With a working-space 2 feet wide, swappable tools like a 3D-Printing head or a router, an optional conveyor belt accessory coming soon, and a sub-$200 price tag, Ottia breaks down the barrier to making for all, allowing everyone to have access to their own personal factory, so that no one gets left behind in this new industrial revolution.

Description: JobPrize is a service that offers a prize when users help someone find a job.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: Would you pay $500 to someone to help you land a $75k a year job? JobPrize is a job referral network that allows Job Seekers to pay informed employees to refer and help them land a job. Jobprize is a Job Referral Network where job seekers can post a profile of their qualifications and be seen by employees willing to give them a referral. In this economy, we need to find new ways to bring unemployment from out of a slump. Companies have open positions that need to be filled, but are not effectively advertised. Job seekers need jobs, but do not have the contacts to refer them, or yet has spent hundreds of hours submitting jobs through websites and filling out applications with no luck. Your best bet? Profile yourself on JobPrize and you are one step closer to being seen by people willing to refer you to a position which you qualify for. Thats the idea behind JobPrize. Job seekers can work within their personal network or allow worldwide Prize Hunters to refer them to a position within the Prize Hunters company. Here is how it works, New College Grads, Seasoned Employees, or Entry Level individuals can sign up for an account at JobPrize.com. Post a profile which includes the type of job being sought. Once submitted, prize hunters can search the site for profiles that matches openings within their industry. If they find one, they can match it up to their company database and refer you, the job seeker to the position. In many instances, companies offer a referral bonus, so the prize hunter can choose to take this bonus directly from their company. Because most jobs are landed through referrals, this will ultimately lead to a more fruitful job search and put our network of prize hunters to work for you cutting hundreds of hours of search time and allowing job seekers to focus on what is important, building your skills. So should you profile yourself on JobPrize and be seen by people willing to give you a referral? Its worth it.

Description: R.E.D. is a second hand retail business that will specialize in smaller, newer electronics.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: R.E.D. is a second hand retail business that will specialize in smaller, newer electronics. This more "defined" version of a second hand retailer will allow us to operate with less overhead and will not look like the typical second hand business with bars on the windows and the clutter of a thrift shop. It will present itself as a sleek, "high-end" retailer that offers services as well as products. The front of the store will feature a "buys" area where the inventory is purchased from the public. Separated from that is the cleaning/pricing station that will also have a small area devoted to repairs. The remainder of the store will be devoted to sales. We will have several glass cases that are accessible from the back only. This will eliminate the need to send an associate across the sales floor to unlock a case. The design of the store will not be "self service" but as close as we can get to it. Any merchandise that can be powered on and displayed, so the customer can see and try the features of the item, will be. Our goal will be to make the entire customer experience as quick and convenient as possible. Our past training and experience tells us to greet everyone that walks in the door. This can be done incorrectly, as I'm sure we have all experienced. Some of our competitors teach this religiously. R.E.D. will certainly acknowledge anyone who walks in the door. This happens to be the best first deterrent to shop-lifters, by the way. But anyone who decides to purchase from us will get the personal attention that most retailers lack. The current attitude in retail has always been attempt an add-on or an up sale but after you have closed the deal then shut up. At R.E.D. we will personally thank every customer that buys from us and the associates will remind them of their names' so they will know who to ask for if they have any questions or problems after the sale. THIS will separate us from most retailers, but it will separate us from ALL second hand retailers.
